-- Comcast Is Developing Service Combining Internet, Television, WSJ Reports
-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 2010-12-13T23:01:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/comcast-is-developing-service-combining-internet-tv-wsj-says.html
Comcast Corp. is developing a
service that combines television and Internet using a new set-
top box, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing unidentified
people familiar with the situation.  The company is conducting a test of the service in Augusta,
Georgia, and may offer it to customers next year, the newspaper
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  